{"Instruction": "Design a system that combines a 4-to-16 decoder with a 4-bit multiplier using the shift-and-add method. The decoder should have a 2-bit input (sel) that selects one of the 16 outputs to be low, while all others are high. The multiplier should have two 4-bit inputs (a and b) and one 8-bit output (the product). The system should also have a clock input and a reset input. The decoder and multiplier should operate independently, but the output of the selected decoder output should be used as one of the inputs to the multiplier. The module should perform the multiplication on the rising edge of the clock signal and reset the product to zero on the rising edge of the reset signal.", "Input": "module top_module (
    input clk,
    input reset,
    input [1:0] sel, // 2-bit input for the decoder
    input [3:0] a, b, // 4-bit inputs for the multiplier
    output reg [7:0] product // 8-bit output from the multiplier
    output reg [15:0] out // 16-bit output from the decoder
);", "Response": ["module top_module (
    input clk,
    input reset,
    input [1:0] sel, // 2-bit input for the decoder
    input [3:0] a, b, // 4-bit inputs for the multiplier
    output reg [7:0] product, // 8-bit output from the multiplier
    output reg [15:0] out // 16-bit output from the decoder
);

reg [15:0] decoder_out;
reg [3:0] multiplier_out;

// 4-to-16 decoder
always @ (sel) begin
    case (sel)
        2'b00: decoder_out = 16'b1111111111111110;
        2'b01: decoder_out = 16'b1111111111111101;
        2'b10: decoder_out = 16'b1111111111111011;
        2'b11: decoder_out = 16'b1111111111110111;
    endcase
end

// 4-bit multiplier using shift-and-add method
always @(posedge clk) begin
    if (reset) begin
        product <= 8'b0;
        multiplier_out <= 4'b0;
    end else begin
        multiplier_out <= a;
        for (i = 0; i < 4; i = i + 1) begin
            if (b[i] == 1) begin
                product <= product + (multiplier_out << i);
            end
        end
    end
end

// Output from selected decoder output used as one of the inputs to the multiplier
always @ (decoder_out, multiplier_out) begin
    case (sel)
        2'b00: product[7:0] <= decoder_out[7:0];
        2'b01: product[7:0] <= decoder_out[15:8];
        2'b10: product[7:0] <= decoder_out[11:4];
        2'b11: product[7:0] <= decoder_out[15:8];
    endcase
end

// Output from the decoder
assign out = decoder_out;

endmodule"]}
{"Instruction": "Please act as a professional Verilog designer. Create a module that compares two 4-bit binary numbers and outputs a 2-bit signal indicating which input is greater. If the first input is greater than the second, the output should be 10. If the second input is greater than the first, the output should be 01. If the two inputs are equal, the output should be 00. The design should also include a module that calculates the bitwise AND of the two inputs. Use a combinational logic architecture to implement the design and a priority encoder to achieve the desired functionality.", "Input": "module comparator_and_and (
