  end

endmodule"]}
{"Instruction": "Design a system that combines the priority encoder from problem 1 with the binary to one-hot converter from problem 2. The system should take in three inputs (A, B, and C) and output a one-hot code corresponding to the priority of the inputs. If all inputs are 0, then O0 should be 1 and all other outputs should be 0. If A is 1 and B and C are 0, then O1 should be 1 and all other outputs should be 0. If B is 1 and A and C are 0, then O2 should be 1 and all other outputs should be 0. If C is 1 and A and B are 0, then O4 should be 1 and all other outputs should be 0. This pattern should continue for all possible input combinations. The system should also include an additional functional module that takes in the outputs of the priority encoder and the binary to one-hot converter and outputs a final 8-bit value. The output should be the value corresponding to the one-hot code of the highest priority input.", "Input": "module top_module (
